parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Collision Avoidance System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the collision avoidance system can cause the vehicle to abruptly stop, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops even when there are no vehicles or objects nearby
the collision avoidance system inappropriately activates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the remote start feature can cause inconvenience and frustration for the vehicle owner, and may also be a selling point for the vehicle.
symptoms: The remote start feature does not function
the vehicle will turn over but immediately die when using the remote start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate speedometer readings can lead to unsafe driving practices, as the driver may not be aware of their actual speed.
symptoms: The speedometer reads lower than the actual speed
the speedometer reading is inconsistent with GPS and radar measurements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning air conditioning can cause discomfort and distraction for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The air conditioning does not function properly
the air conditioning has frequent problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate fuel economy claims can lead to disappointment and financial losses for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The actual fuel economy is lower than the claimed fuel economy
the fuel economy is inconsistent with the listed city
highway
and average mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injector can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes while driving
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the engine misfires or runs rough
the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Module and Fuel Injector Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module and fuel injectors can cause the engine to idle rough, hesitate, or stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The EPC (Electronic Power Control) light and Check Engine warning light illuminate
the vehicle idles rough
the vehicle hesitates or stalls
abnormal sounds come from the engine
the vehicle is belabored while shifting gears
and the vehicle is slow to respond at low speeds.
